# Tailwind Configuration Rules

## Core Principles
- **Design System**: Centralize colors, spacing, typography
- **Content Paths**: Ensure all template files are scanned
- **Extend, Don't Replace**: Preserve default utilities
- **Theme Consistency**: Match project branding

## Theme Extension
- **Colors**: Define project color palette (primary, accent, etc.)
- **Typography**: Custom font families and sizes
- **Spacing**: Custom spacing scale if needed
- **Animations**: Project-specific animations

## Content Configuration
- Include all files containing class names
- Use glob patterns for efficiency
- Don't forget HTML files and dynamic components

## Custom Utilities
- Use `@layer utilities` in CSS for simple additions
- Use plugins for complex custom utilities
- Document non-obvious utility purposes

## Performance
- Minimize content paths scope for faster builds
- Use `safelist` sparingly (increases bundle size)
- Avoid excessive theme customization

## Anti-Patterns
- Don't replace default theme (use `extend`)
- Avoid inline colors/values; use theme tokens
- Don't add unused utilities to safelist
- Avoid deeply nested theme values
